.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor \- NIP\-66 Relay Discovery and Liveness Monitoring
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor;
\&
\&    # Build a relay discovery event (kind 30166)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->discovery_event(
\&        pubkey       => $pubkey,
\&        relay_url    => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com/\*(Aq,
\&        network      => \*(Aqclearnet\*(Aq,
\&        nips         => [1, 11, 42],
\&        rtt_open     => \*(Aq150\*(Aq,
\&        requirements => [\*(Aq!payment\*(Aq, \*(Aqauth\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Build a monitor announcement event (kind 10166)
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->announcement_event(
\&        pubkey    => $pubkey,
\&        frequency => \*(Aq3600\*(Aq,
\&        checks    => [qw(ws nip11 ssl dns)],
\&        timeouts  => [{ test => \*(Aqopen\*(Aq, ms => \*(Aq5000\*(Aq }],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse either kind
\&    my $mon = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->from_event($event);
\&    say $mon\->relay_url;    # discovery events
\&    say $mon\->frequency;    # announcement events
\&
\&    # Validate
\&    Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-66 (Relay Discovery and Liveness Monitoring). Provides
methods to build and parse two event types:
.IP "\fBKind 30166\fR \-\- Relay Discovery Events" 4
.IX Item "Kind 30166 -- Relay Discovery Events"
Addressable events published by monitors documenting relay characteristics
inferred from NIP\-11 documents or probing. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag MUST be set to the
relay\*(Aqs normalized URL (or a hex pubkey for non\-URL relays). The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR
MAY include the stringified JSON of the relay\*(Aqs NIP\-11 document.
.IP "\fBKind 10166\fR \-\- Relay Monitor Announcements" 4
.IX Item "Kind 10166 -- Relay Monitor Announcements"
Replaceable events advertising a monitor\*(Aqs intent to publish discovery
events at a regular frequency.
.PP
Clients MUST NOT require \f(CW30166\fR events to function. Clients SHOULD NOT
trust a single monitor source.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $mon = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\*(C'\fR object. All fields are optional.
Array fields (\f(CW\*(C`nips\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`requirements\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`topics\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`languages\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`timeouts\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`checks\*(C'\fR) default to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR. Croaks on unknown arguments.
Typically returned by "from_event".
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS discovery_event
.IX Subsection "discovery_event"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->discovery_event(
\&        pubkey       => $hex_pubkey,
\&        relay_url    => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com/\*(Aq,
\&        network      => \*(Aqclearnet\*(Aq,
\&        relay_type   => \*(AqPrivateInbox\*(Aq,
\&        nips         => [1, 11, 42],
\&        requirements => [\*(Aq!payment\*(Aq, \*(Aqauth\*(Aq],
\&        topics       => [\*(Aqnsfw\*(Aq],
\&        kinds        => [\*(Aq1\*(Aq, \*(Aq!20000\*(Aq],
\&        geohash      => \*(Aqww8p1r4t8\*(Aq,
\&        languages    => [\*(Aqen\*(Aq],
\&        rtt_open     => \*(Aq234\*(Aq,
\&        rtt_read     => \*(Aq150\*(Aq,
\&        rtt_write    => \*(Aq300\*(Aq,
\&        nip11        => \*(Aq{"name":"My Relay"}\*(Aq,
\&        created_at   => time(),
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 30166 addressable Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR is
required and becomes the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. \f(CW\*(C`nip11\*(C'\fR, if provided, becomes the
event \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR (otherwise empty string). Multi\-value tags (\f(CW\*(C`nips\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`requirements\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`topics\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`languages\*(C'\fR) are emitted as
repeated tags per the spec. Any remaining arguments are passed through
to "new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS announcement_event
.IX Subsection "announcement_event"
.Vb 12
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->announcement_event(
\&        pubkey    => $hex_pubkey,
\&        frequency => \*(Aq3600\*(Aq,
\&        timeouts  => [
\&            { test => \*(Aqopen\*(Aq, ms => \*(Aq5000\*(Aq },
\&            { test => \*(Aqread\*(Aq, ms => \*(Aq3000\*(Aq },
\&            { ms => \*(Aq10000\*(Aq },                  # applies to all tests
\&        ],
\&        checks    => [qw(ws nip11 ssl dns geo)],
\&        geohash   => \*(Aqww8p1r4t8\*(Aq,
\&        created_at => time(),
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 10166 replaceable Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`frequency\*(C'\fR is
required (seconds between publications). \f(CW\*(C`timeouts\*(C'\fR is an arrayref of
hashrefs with \f(CW\*(C`ms\*(C'\fR (milliseconds) and optional \f(CW\*(C`test\*(C'\fR (test type).
When \f(CW\*(C`test\*(C'\fR is omitted, the timeout applies to all tests. \f(CW\*(C`checks\*(C'\fR is
an arrayref of lowercase check names. Any remaining arguments are passed
through to "new" in Net::Nostr::Event.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $mon = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 30166 or 10166 event into a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\*(C'\fR
object. Returns \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the event kind is neither 30166 nor 10166.
.PP
.Vb 8
\&    my $mon = Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->from_event($event);
\&    if ($event\->kind == 30166) {
\&        say $mon\->relay_url;
\&        say $mon\->network;
\&    } else {
\&        say $mon\->frequency;
\&        say join \*(Aq, \*(Aq, @{$mon\->checks};
\&    }
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates a NIP\-66 event. For kind 30166, checks that a \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag is
present. For kind 10166, checks that a \f(CW\*(C`frequency\*(C'\fR tag is present.
Croaks if the kind is unsupported or required tags are missing.
Returns 1 on success.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::RelayMonitor\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
.SS "Discovery Event Fields (kind 30166)"
.IX Subsection "Discovery Event Fields (kind 30166)"
\fIrelay_url\fR
.IX Subsection "relay_url"
.PP
Relay URL from the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag. For non\-URL relays, may be a hex pubkey.
.PP
\fInetwork\fR
.IX Subsection "network"
.PP
Network type. SHOULD be one of \f(CW\*(C`clearnet\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`tor\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`i2p\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`loki\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\fIrelay_type\fR
.IX Subsection "relay_type"
.PP
Relay type in PascalCase (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`PrivateInbox\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\fInips\fR
.IX Subsection "nips"
.PP
Arrayref of supported NIP numbers (as strings).
.PP
\fIrequirements\fR
.IX Subsection "requirements"
.PP
Arrayref of requirement strings. False values use \f(CW\*(C`!\*(C'\fR prefix
(e.g. \f(CW\*(C`!payment\*(C'\fR). Corresponds to NIP\-11 \f(CW\*(C`limitations\*(C'\fR.
.PP
\fItopics\fR
.IX Subsection "topics"
.PP
Arrayref of topic strings.
.PP
\fIkinds\fR
.IX Subsection "kinds"
.PP
Arrayref of accepted/unaccepted kind strings. Unaccepted kinds use
\&\f(CW\*(C`!\*(C'\fR prefix (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`!20000\*(C'\fR).
.PP
\fIgeohash\fR
.IX Subsection "geohash"
.PP
NIP\-52 geohash string. Used by both discovery and announcement events.
.PP
\fIlanguages\fR
.IX Subsection "languages"
.PP
Arrayref of ISO\-639\-1 language codes.
.PP
\fIrtt_open\fR
.IX Subsection "rtt_open"
.PP
Open round\-trip time in milliseconds (string).
.PP
\fIrtt_read\fR
.IX Subsection "rtt_read"
.PP
Read round\-trip time in milliseconds (string).
.PP
\fIrtt_write\fR
.IX Subsection "rtt_write"
.PP
Write round\-trip time in milliseconds (string).
.PP
\fInip11\fR
.IX Subsection "nip11"
.PP
Stringified JSON of the relay\*(Aqs NIP\-11 informational document, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS "Announcement Event Fields (kind 10166)"
.IX Subsection "Announcement Event Fields (kind 10166)"
\fIfrequency\fR
.IX Subsection "frequency"
.PP
Publication frequency in seconds (string).
.PP
\fItimeouts\fR
.IX Subsection "timeouts"
.PP
Arrayref of timeout hashrefs. Each has \f(CW\*(C`ms\*(C'\fR (milliseconds) and optional
\&\f(CW\*(C`test\*(C'\fR (test type). When \f(CW\*(C`test\*(C'\fR is absent, the timeout applies to all
tests.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    # With test type
\&    { test => \*(Aqopen\*(Aq, ms => \*(Aq5000\*(Aq }
\&
\&    # Without test type (applies to all)
\&    { ms => \*(Aq5000\*(Aq }
.Ve
.PP
\fIchecks\fR
.IX Subsection "checks"
.PP
Arrayref of lowercase check name strings (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`ws\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nip11\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`ssl\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`dns\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`geo\*(C'\fR).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-66 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/66.md>,
Net::Nostr::RelayInfo, Net::Nostr, Net::Nostr::Event
